Since use the `np.random.randint` (see line 268 and 279),  which return random integers in the “half-open” interval [low, high).   Lead to the last parameter is always fixed.

The test example:

```python
import ConfigSpace as CS
import ConfigSpace.hyperparameters as CSH
from ConfigSpace.util import get_random_neighbor

cs = CS.ConfigurationSpace(seed=10)
a = CSH.CategoricalHyperparameter('a', choices=[1, 2])
b = CSH.CategoricalHyperparameter('b', choices=[3, 4])
c = CSH.CategoricalHyperparameter('c', choices=[5, 6])

cs.add_hyperparameters([a, b, c])

configuration = cs.get_default_configuration()
for i in range(12):
    configuration = get_random_neighbor(configuration, i)
    print(configuration.get_dictionary())
```

